    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Offering a driver-focused 2004 BMW M3 (E46) featuring the high-revving S54B32 inline-six. This unit utilizes a high-pressure Double VANOS variable valve timing system and six individual throttle bodies to achieve a linear power band up to its 8,000 RPM redline. Power is sent to the rear wheels via a Getrag 6-speed manual gearbox and a torque-sensing Variable M Differential Lock. Mechanical integrity is prioritized: the rod bearing service is documented, and the rear subframe has been reinforced to mitigate common floor-pan fatigue. The suspension retains its factory geometry with refreshed bushings for precise turn-in. While showing minor cosmetic patina consistent with a well-loved driver, its mechanical synchronization is excellent.",
